        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> I found that the camp is easy. Just go inside invis (CoS rules here), past the double door, through the underwater tunnel. As you come to surface, there is one spawn there. I just summoned a pet and pulled everything from there until clear, the parked pet in Ishva's room. When she spawned (green at 54) the tried the whole fight to fear me .. LoL. How stupid can this gnoll be ? :) Anyway, pet tore her apart.</P><P>BTW, keep ST memmed. Great for adds, and great for interrupting those stupid healers. Use lower level darkness to snare everything you fight(Engulfing or Clinging). Shadowpact and BoD are your friends too, although the 49 pet can take quite a bit of abuse. Very few roamers, so if things get bad, use pet command /pet let_those_5_gnolls_slaughter_you_while_I_get_the_fuck_away , FD, wait for them to return to spawn spots and try again. </P><P>If you did Dalnir at 44, you wont have any problems :)</P><P>EDIT: Nothing inside sees invis, so go scout first, see where they are, con them, see what you can single pull, check for way out, etc. You know the drill :-)</P><P>---<BR>Iranicus Darkseeker<BR>Defiler of Cold Comfort<BR>Ayonae Ro<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12328" target="_blank">My Gear</a></P><P>Edited by - Iranicus on 03/12/2002  03:12:12</font></td>
